{{Quote|I knew I loved to write, and I occasionally dared to hope that someday, my writing would be more than a secret pleasure.|Deborah J. Ross|<ref name="About Me">{{WebCite|url=https://deborahjross.com/about-us/|text=About Me|work=Deborahjross.com|author=[[Deborah J. Ross]]|archivedate=20250618091926}}</ref>}}
'''Deborah J. Ross''', who previously wrote under her married name of '''Deborah Wheeler''', is an [[Wikipedia:Americans|American]] author. She wrote the short story "[[Goatgrass: The Tale of Ree-Yees]]" for the [[1995]] ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'' anthology.

Outside of ''[[Star Wars]]'', Ross has written a number of novels and short stories. She was collaborating with [[Wikipedia:Marion Zimmer Bradley|Marion Zimmer Bradley]] on the [[Wikipedia:Darkover series|''Darkover'' series]] when Bradley passed away, and Ross continued the series in her honor. She has also served as Secretary for the [[Wikipedia:Science Fiction and Fantasy Writers Association|Science Fiction and Fantasy Writers Association]] and as Liaison to the [[Wikipedia:Worldcon|World Science Fiction Convention]], and she is an advocate for the abolition of the death penalty.<ref name="About Me" />

